    <h1>Information on Basal Metabolic Rate</h1>

    <h4>
        The quantity of calories your body requires to sustain essential physiological
        processes, such as breathing, circulation, cell creation, and nutrient digestion,
        when at rest is known as your Basal Metabolic Rate, or BMR.
        It is basically the energy needed to sustain life in
        your body in the absence of physical exertion or digestion.
    </h4>
