    <div class="mx-auto">
        <Card TextAlignment="Alignment.Center" Style="border-color = black; border-radius = 23px" >
            <CardTitle>Factors Influencing BMR</CardTitle>
            <br />
            <p>
                <ul><strong>Age:</strong> BMR tends to decrease with age due to loss of muscle mass and hormonal changes.</ul>
                <ul><strong>Sex:</strong> Males generally have a higher BMR than females, largely due to higher muscle mass.</ul>
                <ul>
                    <strong>Body Composition:</strong>
                    More muscle mass increases BMR, as muscle tissue burns more calories at rest compared to fat tissue.
                </ul>
                <ul><strong>Genetics:</strong> Some people naturally have a higher or lower BMR due to genetic factors.</ul>
                <ul>
                    <strong>Hormonal Factors:</strong> Thyroid hormones play a significant role in regulating metabolism.
                    Conditions like hypothyroidism can lower BMR, while hyperthyroidism can raise it.
                </ul>
                <ul>
                    <strong>Environmental Temperature:</strong>
                    Extreme temperatures can slightly increase BMR as the body works to maintain its core temperature.
                </ul>
            </p>
        </Card>
    </div>
